race.comment: Strong Super Maiden with plenty of chances. SEQUISTA (13) classy filly who can go one better today second-up. Closed strongly as the dominant ($1.60 fav), when a narrow second over 1100m at Wyong. Strips fitter and the cross-over nose band comes off. Hard to stop. ESCARGOES (3) showed good early dash on resumption before knocking up late when second over 1180m at Gundagai. Senior rider goes on as well as the blinkers. Leading prospect. HARRY'S HALO (5) deep into the prep and expect to see him race a little closer from the good gate today. Strong through the line when second over 1200m at this track. Close to that elusive Maiden victory. PYROLYSIS (12) continued where she left off last campaign when a tough on-pace second over 1100m at Canterbury. Doesn't get the same map favour here but must be respected.
